Vector addition is performed through C++

N_OPS and N_ENTRIES can be given as first input.(Error handling is done such that these are positive values)
N_OPS denotes number of Vector additions can be performed
N_ENTRIES denote number of integer values in a vector

Later with number of operations and number of entries, sum vectors for each 2 vectors can be displayed in output.

NOTE: As per the requirement only pair of vectors can be added. Three or more vector addition is not allowed, once you enter 2 vectors then immediately sum vector is printed in output, then one can give next pair of vectors if N_OPS is greater than one.

All memory is dynamically allocated and released before termination.